@startuml dkey_access_to_tgm_tailgate_state_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title DKEY Access To TGM Tailgate State Signal Flow\n(DKEY access + tailgate control -> TGM tailgate-state publication)

participant "Tailgate control source\nassist / open request / actuator" as Ctrl #F4F7FB
participant "DKEY\nVehicleAccessState / KeyPresence" as DKEY #E8F0FE
participant "Vehicle state\nDriveState" as Veh #E8F0FE
participant "TGM\ntailgate owner" as TGM #FFF4CC
participant "Body observers /\npanel readback" as Obs #FCE8FF

== Tailgate Inputs ==

Ctrl -> TGM : frmPowerTailgateCtrlStateMsg\nTailgateAssistMode / OpenRequestState / TailgateActuatorCmd
DKEY -> TGM : frmDigitalKeyStateMsg\nVehicleAccessState / KeyPresence
Veh -> TGM : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\nDriveState
activate TGM
TGM -> TGM : normalize stale control / DKEY / vehicle inputs
TGM -> TGM : accessAuthorized when drive=0\nand DKEY access/key conditions are met
TGM -> TGM : derive TailgateLockState / OpenState
TGM -> TGM : derive TailgatePowerState / TailgatePosition
note right of TGM
Representative conditions
- DriveState == 0
- KeyPresence == 1
- VehicleAccessState >= 1
- assist / request / actuator command valid
end note

== Tailgate Publish ==

TGM -> Obs : frmTailgateStateMsg
TGM -> Obs : traceable tailgate lock/open/power state
deactivate TGM

note over Ctrl, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Tailgate control command arrives with DKEY access context
2. TGM validates park/access authorization
3. TGM derives lock, open, power, and position state
4. Body observers and tests confirm the tailgate outcome
end note

@enduml
